<dl id="n10069d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10069d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10069d"> 69(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> whistled language / flag &mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Tamerlan, le c&eacute;l&egrave;bre conqu&eacute;rant tartare (1336-1405), <mark>se servait de drapeaux pour dicter</mark> ses conditions aux villes assi&eacute;g&eacute;es. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> LE LANGAGE SIFFL&Eacute; <font color="green">[Tamerlane, the famous Tartar conqueror (1336&ndash;1405) used flags to communicate his terms to besieged cities. [&hellip;]</font> WHISTLED LANGUAGE] <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 304</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
